Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "obala" (shore) in different forms and positions:

1. Volim da šetam uz *obalu* reke. (I love to walk along the *shore* of the river.)
2. Prošli smo kroz malo *obalno* mesto na putu do plaže. (We passed through a small *coastal* town on our way to the beach.)
3. Nisam siguran da li smo na pravoj *obali* jezera. (I'm not sure if we're on the right *shore* of the lake.)
4. Večeras ćemo se prošetati duž *obale* mora i uživati u zalasku sunca. (Tonight we'll take a walk along the *shore* of the sea and enjoy the sunset.)
5. Zelenilo na *obali* reke čini ovaj kraj još lepšim. (The greenery on the *shore* of the river makes this area even more beautiful.)

In all of these sentences, the word "obala" refers to a shore or coastline in some way. The star indicates the exact word in Serbian that corresponds to "shore" in English.